SELECT
  count(timestamp) AS c,
  toStartOfInterval(timestamp, INTERVAL (($__toTime - $__fromTime) / 36) SECOND ) AS d
FROM realtime_logs
WHERE   ( timestamp  >= $__fromTime AND timestamp <= $__toTime )
AND x_edge_result_type = 'Hit'
GROUP BY d
ORDER BY d ASC

SELECT
  count(timestamp) AS c,
  toStartOfInterval(timestamp, INTERVAL (($__toTime - $__fromTime) / 36) SECOND ) AS d
FROM realtime_logs
WHERE   ( timestamp  >= $__fromTime AND timestamp <= $__toTime )
AND x_edge_result_type = 'Miss'
GROUP BY d
ORDER BY d ASC

SELECT 
sc_status as category,
count(sc_status)
FROM canopy."realtime_logs" 
WHERE   ( timestamp  >= $__fromTime AND timestamp <= $__toTime ) 
GROUP BY category
ORDER BY category

SELECT
  sum(sc_bytes) AS content_bytes,
  sum(cs_bytes) AS client_bytes,
  toStartOfInterval(timestamp, INTERVAL (($__toTime - $__fromTime) / 20) SECOND ) AS d
FROM realtime_logs
WHERE   ( timestamp  >= $__fromTime AND timestamp <= $__toTime )
GROUP BY d
ORDER BY d ASC

panels.description: This table shows a list of the top 10 URIs by request, irrespective of whether the request result was a hit or miss.

targets.rawSql: SELECT cs_uri_stem URI, count(*) Count FROM canopy."realtime_logs" WHERE   ( timestamp  >= $__fromTime AND timestamp <= $__toTime ) GROUP BY cs_uri_stem ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 10
